repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
Apply it to a few tests, and do some small limited api fixes.

This is mainly intended to make it easier to test more stuff - the fixes here are pretty minor.

comment_data.body: I've started writing a cleanup to at least avoid needing this in the `.proto` part. It should be enough to include it in the impl section. We can then exclude these changes from this PR.
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -1,8 +1,12 @@
 /////////////// TypeConversions.proto ///////////////
-//@requires: StringTools.c::IncludeStringH
 
 /* Type Conversion Predeclarations */
 
+// Note that this is *always* included in the module preamble
+// (but the impl part is only generated on demand).
+// Therefore IncludeStringH is not be reliable
+#include <string.h>

comment_data.body: Hmm, then why don't *we*  set `Py_LIMITED_API` in the tests and instead need a new macro guard? The `CYTHON_*` macro names are specifically meant for users to define. I would leave it to `runtests.py` to set `Py_LIMITED_API` to something reasonable.
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -1,6 +1,10 @@
 /////////////// InitLimitedAPI ///////////////
 
-#if defined(CYTHON_LIMITED_API) && 0  /* disabled: enabling Py_LIMITED_API needs more work */
+#if defined(CYTHON_LIMITED_API) && defined(CYTHON_TEST_IN_LIMITED_API)
+  /* disabled by default: enabling Py_LIMITED_API needs more work.
+     Users should not define CYTHON_TEST_IN_LIMITED_API since it will
+     be removed when support is better.
+     If you want Py_LIMITED_API then set it yourself for now */

@@ -1,8 +1,12 @@
 /////////////// TypeConversions.proto ///////////////
-//@requires: StringTools.c::IncludeStringH
 
 /* Type Conversion Predeclarations */
 
+// Note that this is *always* included in the module preamble
+// (but the impl part is only generated on demand).
+// Therefore IncludeStringH is not be reliable
+#include <string.h>

commit.message:
Add test tag turning on Py_LIMITED_API

Apply it to a few tests, and do some small limited api fixes.
Switch to allowed list of tests
